bug.short_desc: berkeley db deadlocks during environment shutdown/startup

long_desc.thetext: berkeley db seems to like to deadlock during environment startup. this shows up as the master process not accepting any more connections, since it's waiting for imapds to initialize their environment so they can accept a connection.
Created an attachment (id=1) strace of deadlock situation on solaris
Created an attachment (id=2) commented trace saying where in mboxlist_close/mboxlist_done things are
Created an attachment (id=4) sample program showing environment deadlock
Created an attachment (id=5) patch from Keith Bostic hopefully solving deadlocks
keith's patch seems to prevent the sample program from deadlocking. closing for now.
